//Here’s a simple plan for integrating APIs into your travel app for tourists:

//  Useful APIs:-

//For a travel app, useful APIs could include:

//Google Maps API – For maps, places, directions, and geolocation services.

//OpenWeatherMap API – To provide weather updates.

//TripAdvisor API or Yelp API – For nearby attractions, hotels, restaurants.

//Currency Conversion APIs – Like Fixer.io API for live exchange rates.

//Flight / Hotel Booking APIs – Like Amadeus or Skyscanner API for booking information.

//Public Transport APIs – For local transport info (depends on the country or city).


Google Maps API
1️⃣ Register and get an API key:

Visit Google Cloud Console
.

Create a project and enable Maps JavaScript API and Places API.

Get the API key.

2️⃣ Sample HTML + JavaScript Code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Tourist Travel App Map</title>
    <script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=YOUR_API_KEY&libraries=places"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Tourist Guide Map</h1>
    <div id="map" style="height: 500px; width: 100%;"></div>

    <script>
        function initMap() {
            const touristSpot = { lat: 48.8584, lng: 2.2945 };  // Example: Eiffel Tower
            const map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById('map'), {
                zoom: 14,
                center: touristSpot
            });
            const marker = new google.maps.Marker({
                position: touristSpot,
                map: map,
                title: 'Eiffel Tower'
            });
        }

        window.onload = initMap;
    </script>
</body>
</html>
